    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Liturgical vestments comprising a shield-shaped panel of embroidery, artificially stiffened and sometimes adorned with a fringe, attached to the back of the cope. Cope shields evolved from the cappa or hood on the oldest form of copes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
